# SKILL.md Entry Point Format

## Required YAML Frontmatter

Every SKILL.md must start with:

```yaml
---
name: skill-name-here
description: What the skill does and when to use it. Use when...
---
```

### `name` field
- Max 64 characters
- Lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only
- Use gerund form preferred: `processing-pdfs`, `creating-checkout`
- No reserved words: "anthropic", "claude"
- No XML tags

### `description` field
- Max 1024 characters, non-empty
- Write in third person ("Processes Excel files", not "I can help you process")
- Include BOTH what the skill does AND when to trigger it
- Include specific keywords users might say (e.g. "checkout", "payment", "billing")

Bad: `description: Helps with documents`
Good: `description: Extract text and tables from PDF files, fill forms, merge documents. Use when working with PDF files or when the user mentions PDFs, forms, or document extraction.`

## Body Structure

- Keep under 500 lines. Split into reference files if approaching this limit.
- Start with a brief heading and one-line summary.
- Include a **Quick start** section or core concepts near the top.
- Link to detailed reference files for advanced features: `See [FORMS.md](FORMS.md) for complete guide`
- Include an **Implementation Checklist** with trackable progress:

```
Task Progress:
- [ ] Step 1: ...
- [ ] Step 2: ...
```

## Online Documentation References

When a skill references external docs (Solvapay API docs, SDK docs), use the **online-first with local fallback** pattern:

1. Link to live docs first so the agent fetches the latest version
2. Bundle a **Fallback Reference** section or file with essential API details for when docs are unreachable
3. Never rely solely on online docs -- the agent's runtime may lack network access

```markdown
## Documentation

Fetch the latest docs before implementing:
- **API Reference**: https://docs.solvapay.com/api/checkout

If unavailable, use the fallback reference below (or in [reference.md](reference.md)).
```

For well-known third-party tools (Supabase, Tailwind), linking to their docs without a fallback is acceptable -- the agent already has training knowledge as a baseline.

## Progressive Disclosure

SKILL.md is a table of contents. It should overview and route, not contain everything.

- Point to sub-files for detailed guides, reference docs, and examples
- Keep references ONE level deep (SKILL.md -> reference.md, never reference.md -> details.md)
- Name files descriptively: `form_validation_rules.md`, not `doc2.md`
